        "summary":  "Organizations must move beyond celebrating AI capabilities to actively managing its consumption-based economics, as AI costs accumulate through millions of interactions rather than flat licensing fees. Unlike traditional software, a single model upgrade can silently multiply token consumption across an entire enterprise without a formal budget decision. Companies that govern both what they build and what they spend on AI will be best positioned to scale confidently.",
