        "summary":  "CIOs face a fundamental tension between accelerating AI adoption and managing governance risks that conventional IT controls cannot address, because AI behavior is indeterminate rather than deterministic. Organizations that establish independent compliance teams separate from innovation teams ΓÇö creating healthy internal tensions ΓÇö gain competitive advantage over those using reactive, approval-based governance. Delaying employee access to sanctioned AI tools paradoxically increases risk by driving shadow adoption outside official oversight channels.",
